
QUÆSUMUS, Dómine, pro tua pietáte miserére ánimæ fámulæ tuæ <sr>N.</s>: et a contágiis mortalitátis exútam, in ætérnæ salvatiónis partem restítue. Per Dóminum.
WE BESEECH the, O Lord, to have pity, in thy great mercy, on the soul of thy handmaid <sr>N.</s>; and do thou, who hast freed her from the perils of this mortal life, vouchsafe to number her for evermore among thy Saints. Through our Lord.
